01:30:20.248 --> 01:30:22.333
- Okay.
- And it gets you backstage with the governor.

01:30:22.417 --> 01:30:25.336
- Where am I supposed to meet them? What room?
- There are only about five.

01:30:25.420 --> 01:30:27.254
- I-I-I —
- You don't know?

01:30:27.339 --> 01:30:30.007
In the director's office of the State House.

01:30:30.092 --> 01:30:32.676
But it's almost impossible to get there
because there are so many...

01:30:32.761 --> 01:30:34.762
tens of thousands of people
out on the street.

01:30:34.846 --> 01:30:37.431
I'll meet you out here.
I'm just going to use the ladies' room.

01:30:37.516 --> 01:30:39.850
[Carville] We don't know how we're
gonna get there through the crowd.

01:30:39.935 --> 01:30:43.104
♪♪ [Rock: Man Singing]

01:30:48.193 --> 01:30:51.112
- [Carville] Excuse me, please. Excuse me.
- [Mandy] That one girl got in.

01:30:51.196 --> 01:30:54.949
Excuse me. Excuse me, please.
Thank you. Thank you very much.

01:30:55.033 --> 01:30:57.284
I'm very proud to have done this.

01:30:57.369 --> 01:31:00.204
I'm as happy as I can be
and I'm so proud.

01:31:01.289 --> 01:31:03.207
We won Nevada big.

01:31:03.291 --> 01:31:06.877
Governor, we're gonna —
I mean, it's looking like close to 400.

01:31:07.462 --> 01:31:09.088
It's a landslide.

01:31:10.215 --> 01:31:13.467
Ohio's not called yet.
North Carolina's not called yet.

01:31:13.552 --> 01:31:15.970
But everything else —
I mean, Michigan —

01:31:17.139 --> 01:31:20.307
Dead even in Florida.
You know, it's just unbelievable.

01:31:20.392 --> 01:31:23.644
You oughta be the —
I mean, the happiest man in the world.

01:31:24.479 --> 01:31:26.856
And I just gotta tell you,
I just appreciate this so much.

01:31:26.940 --> 01:31:28.816
This was the best thing I ever did.

01:31:32.445 --> 01:31:34.572
We can try. He's up there talking now
though, you know.

01:31:34.656 --> 01:31:37.825
He's up there giving his speech. Yep.

01:31:40.495 --> 01:31:41.996
You don't?

01:31:43.582 --> 01:31:45.082
But the one thing you gotta be —

01:31:45.167 --> 01:31:47.543
We really want you to say
whatever you want to say tonight...

01:31:47.627 --> 01:31:50.462
but you just gotta be careful
about being too programmatic.

01:31:50.547 --> 01:31:54.258
You should definitely be New Democrat,
and we love Hillary's new patriotism thing...

01:31:54.342 --> 01:31:56.260
which he tried to put in there.

01:31:56.344 --> 01:31:59.430
Also you gotta do at the end,
he goes back to the announcement speech...

01:31:59.514 --> 01:32:01.432
which is very important.

01:32:02.475 --> 01:32:04.143
But you know, just say what —

01:32:04.227 --> 01:32:06.770
Speak from your heart tonight.
I mean, that's all that matters.

01:32:06.855 --> 01:32:09.356
Say what you want to say.
I mean, this is your night.

01:32:10.775 --> 01:32:12.568
Okay. We'll see you in a little bit.

01:32:12.652 --> 01:32:13.986
Bye-bye.

01:32:14.487 --> 01:32:16.614
- He's like —
- What, is he gone?

01:32:16.698 --> 01:32:19.742
He's asking...
"I think we got Nevada!"

01:32:19.826 --> 01:32:23.621
[All Laughing]

01:32:23.705 --> 01:32:25.789
- Follow Richard.
- [Chattering]

01:32:25.874 --> 01:32:27.875
- Follow Richard.
- Okay, Richard knows where he's going here.

01:32:27.959 --> 01:32:30.127
He's pretty pumped.
I mean, it's unbelievable.

01:32:30.795 --> 01:32:32.504
- He should be.
- Yeah.

01:32:33.298 --> 01:32:35.382
What did he say when you said
"Mr. President"?

01:32:35.467 --> 01:32:36.967
- He said, "Thanks."
- He said, "Yeah, yeah, yeah."

01:32:37.052 --> 01:32:40.304
- "Yeah, yeah. How'd we do in Nevada?"
- [Both Laughing]

01:32:40.388 --> 01:32:41.889
[Crowd Cheering, Applauding]

01:32:41.973 --> 01:32:43.641
And finally I want to thank...

01:32:43.725 --> 01:32:48.145
the members of my brilliant,
aggressive, unconventional...

01:32:48.230 --> 01:32:50.940
but always winning campaign staff.

01:32:51.024 --> 01:32:54.235
[Cheering]

01:33:03.078 --> 01:33:04.828
[Clinton]
And they have earned this.

01:33:04.913 --> 01:33:09.291
♪♪ [Pop]

